full_text: The common business cases for an activity is either to do, an action, or to reveal, verify or inspect, something related to an account, policy or job. First login is an underwriter assistant, Dennis Wright. Open the account Wright construction, and create a new commercial auto submission. Enter required information. Create a new vehicle. Go back to the commercial auto line page. The product model is synchronized and the liability coverage is added. Quote the submission. The current user Dennis Wright is an underwriter assistant. The underwriter, Alice Applegate, must review the submission to accurately assess the risk, before it can be bound. Go to Actions and select New Activity, Underwriting Review, Review and Approve. In the Assign to field, search for or select Alice Applegate. Click OK to create the activity. Log out. Log back in as Alice Applegate. Go to My Activities. The new activity, Review and Approve, is listed. It has a due date, priority, etc. Click the subject link. It opens the activity and its associated policy. The user can review it and click Complete to close the activity. This is the end of demonstration for creating an activity. Filogy of theount of theount of  so
